        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 1:46AM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 146 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Northville, or 13 miles north of Gloversville, moving east at 60 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Northville, Fairchilds Corners, Tenantville, Sweets Crossing, Lake
Luzerne, Pinnacle, Kings Station, Kings, Greenfield Center,
Conklingville, North Greenfield, Maple Grove, Porter Corners,
Carpenters Corners, Tomantown, Osbourne Bridge, Corinth, Lake
Luzerne-Hadley, West Day, and Batchellerville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
